It is observable‚ that the argumentor preface of this piece‚ as given by Mr. Kennedy, makes the number of huntera 3000, whereas the poem, written in his own hand, has only 1000, which corresponds with the MS. of the Dean.. Mr. Ken- nedy’s arguments, indeed, are frequently at variance with the poems to which they are prefixed3 a mistake that may have probably resulted from a disposition in the reciter to exaggerate the subject of the poem in his preliminary account of it.

The two last lines of the following stanza are even more happi- ly expressed in Kennedy’s edition than in his.

Chunnaic e righ Eirean Shios ar lar a chatha

Is thug ruathar chui ge Mar bhuinne re caraig.
